00:54:43.170 --> 00:54:46.360
So I think one is what do
you do in your charitable

00:54:46.360 --> 00:54:48.370
giving as a person.

00:54:48.370 --> 00:54:51.760
I think second is in
terms of your involvement

00:54:51.760 --> 00:54:55.120
in your activism, in
voting, in being involved.

00:54:55.120 --> 00:54:58.940
Whether you're a citizen or not,
you have the freedom of speech.

00:54:58.940 --> 00:55:00.700
The right to vote
is the one part

00:55:00.700 --> 00:55:04.470
that only a citizen can
do in the United States.

00:55:04.470 --> 00:55:06.900
And then I would
encourage you as people

00:55:06.900 --> 00:55:11.220
who work in one of the most
powerful and influential

00:55:11.220 --> 00:55:14.490
companies in the world is to
develop products and services

00:55:14.490 --> 00:55:17.970
that can facilitate
human communication,

00:55:17.970 --> 00:55:20.940
human participation,
and to be really

00:55:20.940 --> 00:55:24.990
watchful of those ways in which
your technologies can create

00:55:24.990 --> 00:55:27.570
a backdoor towards
abusing people's rights.

00:55:27.570 --> 00:55:31.020
And I think that's a place
where Google employees have

00:55:31.020 --> 00:55:34.800
a disproportionate role
or influence in terms

00:55:34.800 --> 00:55:38.040
of making sure that your
technology facilitates

00:55:38.040 --> 00:55:41.940
human liberty and equality,
